  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROGRAMME EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities including but not limited to:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Market the programme to SMEs, institutions of higher learning, students and external partners through telemarketing and events including career fairs, talks, field trips, etc.</li><li>Handle inquiries on programme from external parties</li><li>Evaluate applications based on the programme criteria</li><li>Conduct interviews, shortlist candidates and facilitate matching between applicants and participating companies</li><li>Follow-up and monitor the status of applicants, study award matches and grant funding through working closely with participating companies</li><li>Provide day-to-day administrative support which includes collation of information, processing applications, maintenance of applicants’ database and records, generating reports, preparation of documents and filling, etc.</li><li>Other ad-hoc duties assigned</li></ul><p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Preferably a Diploma holder with at least 1-2 years of working experience. (Fresh Graduates may apply)</li><li>An extrovert and vibrant personality would be an value - add</li><li>Posses strong planning and organizing skill</li><li>A good team player and results-oriented</li><li>Proficient in MS Office Applications: Word, Excel and Powerpoint</li></ul>",
